## Key Principles

- **Plan before building**: Use plan mode for non-trivial tasks, even when they look simple at first glance.
- **Replace, don't deprecate**: Remove old code. No backward-compat shims, re-exports, or `# removed` comments.

## Git Workflow

- Never commit directly to main (enforced by hook).
- Branch naming: `feat/`, `fix/`, `refactor/`, `chore/`, `docs/` prefixes.
- Merge to main with `--no-ff` to preserve branch history.

## Toolkit

This project uses claude-toolkit hooks and skills for Claude Code configuration.

- **Hooks**: `.claude/hooks/` — guardrails enforced automatically (dangerous commands, feature branch, secrets)
- **Skills**: `.claude/skills/` — invoke skills by name (e.g. `/brainstorm-idea`, `/review-plan`)
- **Memories**: `.claude/memories/` — persistent context loaded at session start

Resources may reference skills or agents from the full toolkit that aren't included here. Ignore any `/skill-name` or agent references you don't recognize — they're not available in this distribution.
